  "texts": [
    "At each DW, the sublattice potential varies linearly over a length 2w, and reaches +∆ max (-∆ max) in the 'bulk' of region L (R).To treat this spatially inhomogeneous system, we have to generalize the HF algorithm to allow for translational symmetry breaking.",
    "The system can fully break translation symmetry along the a 1 direction, but we enforce moiré translation symmetry along the a 2 direction.",
    "As a result, the HF projector takes the form ⟨ĉ † τ as (k 1, k 2)ĉ τ ′ a ′ s ′ (k ′ 1, k ′ 2)⟩ = δ k2,k ′ 2 P k ′ 1 τ ′ a ′ s ′;k1τ as (k 2).",
    "(118 Fixed Hilbert Space MethodThe presence of an explicit translation symmetry-breaking potential ∆(r) suggests that we need to rediagonalize the BM model with this term.",
    "The large gap between the central bands and remote bands enables an alternative and simpler approach called the \"Fixed Hilbert space\" method."
  ],
